{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.41",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 41,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 41",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 41 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:1",
      "text": "“Can you draw out Leviathan with a fishhook, or press down his tongue with a cord?",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:2",
      "text": "Can you put a rope in his nose, or pierce his jaw with a hook?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:3",
      "text": "Will he make many supplications to you? Will he speak to you soft words?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:4",
      "text": "Will he make a covenant with you to take him for your servant for ever?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:5",
      "text": "Will you play with him as with a bird, or will you put him on leash for your maidens?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:6",
      "text": "Will traders bargain over him? Will they divide him up among the merchants?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:7",
      "text": "Can you fill his skin with harpoons, or his head with fishing spears?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:8",
      "text": "Lay hands on him; think of the battle; you will not do it again!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:9",
      "text": "Behold, the hope of a man is disappointed; he is laid low even at the sight of him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:10",
      "text": "No one is so fierce that he dares to stir him up. Who then is he that can stand before me?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:11",
      "text": "Who has given to me, that I should repay him? Whatever is under the whole heaven is mine.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:12",
      "text": "“I will not keep silence concerning his limbs, or his mighty strength, or his goodly frame.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:13",
      "text": "Who can strip off his outer garment? Who can penetrate his double coat of mail?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:14",
      "text": "Who can open the doors of his face? Round about his teeth is terror.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:15",
      "text": "His back is made of rows of shields, shut up closely as with a seal.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:16",
      "text": "One is so near to another that no air can come between them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:17",
      "text": "They are joined one to another; they clasp each other and cannot be separated.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:18",
      "text": "His sneezings flash forth light, and his eyes are like the eyelids of the dawn.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:19",
      "text": "Out of his mouth go flaming torches; sparks of fire leap forth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:20",
      "text": "Out of his nostrils comes forth smoke, as from a boiling pot and burning rushes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:21",
      "text": "His breath kindles coals, and a flame comes forth from his mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:22",
      "text": "In his neck abides strength, and terror dances before him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:23",
      "text": "The folds of his flesh cleave together, firmly cast upon him and immovable.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:24",
      "text": "His heart is hard as a stone, hard as the nether millstone.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:25",
      "text": "When he raises himself up the mighty are afraid; at the crashing they are beside themselves.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:26",
      "text": "Though the sword reaches him, it does not avail; nor the spear, the dart, or the javelin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:27",
      "text": "He counts iron as straw, and bronze as rotten wood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:28",
      "text": "The arrow cannot make him flee; for him slingstones are turned to stubble.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:29",
      "text": "Clubs are counted as stubble; he laughs at the rattle of javelins.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:30",
      "text": "His underparts are like sharp potsherds; he spreads himself like a threshing sledge on the mire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:31",
      "text": "He makes the deep boil like a pot; he makes the sea like a pot of ointment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:32",
      "text": "Behind him he leaves a shining wake; one would think the deep to be hoary.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:33",
      "text": "Upon earth there is not his like, a creature without fear.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.41.34",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:34",
      "text": "He beholds everything that is high; he is king over all the sons of pride.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
